commit.message: README: mention you need to do more than update :collection
README: update description of default icon background treatment
README: kind-icon-default-face is no longer needed by default

Protect faces from :background = nil

A nil :background is not a valid face attribute, but is used to signal
to svg-lib to omit background color from svg icons.  Guard against
styling the icon or flanking padding with :background nil.

commit.message:
Work around eglot/lsp-mode disagreement enum-member+type-parameter

eglot uses e.g. enummember, lsp-mode uses enum-member.  The LSP
protocol mentions these in CamelCase so it's not clear which should be
preferred, but snake-case was adopted.  We support both until eglot's
fixes are more widely propagated.  See: company-mode/company-mode#1370.
